<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="254" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d254">
                                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                                    <persName corresp="#p_THS1">Truman</persName> Papers</note>
                                <head>No. 254<lb/><hi rend="italic">Note by the President’s Chief of
                                        Staff</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_LFAWD1"><hi rend="italic">Leahy</hi></persName>)<note n="1" xml:id="d254fn1">Printed from the ribbon copy, which is unsigned.</note>
                                </head>
                                <opener>
                                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-sibling-dates" calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-04">Undated</date>.]</dateline>
                                </opener>
                                <p rend="center">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Korea</hi>
                                </p>
                                <p>Recommend a four power agreement that upon the defeat of
                                        <persName corresp="#p_J1">Japan</persName> Korea be placed
                                    under a trusteeship composed of China, Great Britain, the Soviet
                                    Republic [<hi rend="italic">sic</hi>], and the United States for
                                        <pb facs="0447" n="315" xml:id="pg_315"/> so long a time as
                                    is necessary for it to demonstrate, and until it shall have
                                    demonstrated, its capacity to govern itself as a free and
                                    independent sovereign state.</p>
                            </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>